parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, which can lead to accidents, traffic violations, and decreased vehicle safety.
symptoms: the speedometer needle falls off the dashboard
the speedometer displays incorrect or inconsistent readings

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of rear axle components, such as the bevel pinion and gear, spacer drive bevel, or right axle bearing, can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to other vehicle components.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations from the rear axle
difficulty steering or maintaining control of the vehicle
failure of the rear axle to transmit power to the wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the undercarriage frame welds can cause the vehicle to lose structural integrity, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially severe injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the rear door latch can cause the door to not stay latched, leading to accidents or injuries, especially if the door opens while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: Plastic portion of the rear door latch melts

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Rollover and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of control and rollover of the vehicle can cause severe injuries or fatalities, especially if seatbelts are not used.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Vapor Ingress into Vehicle Cabin
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ingress of fuel vapor into the vehicle cabin can cause discomfort, nausea, and dizziness to occupants, and potentially lead to accidents due to driver distraction or impairment.
symptoms: Fuel vapor odor inside the vehicle
fuel vapor visible inside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck EGR valve can cause the engine to run rough, decrease fuel efficiency, and increase emissions, potentially leading to engine damage and decreased vehicle performance.
A failed thermostat can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, decreased vehicle performance, and potentially causing accidents due to loss of power or engine seizure.
symptoms: temperature gauge in the red zone
engine stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed ECM can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to decreased vehicle performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially causing accidents due to loss of power or engine seizure.
symptoms: Engine stalling or failure to start

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear suspension/alignment issues can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also lead to uneven tire wear, reducing the overall safety and performance of the vehicle.
Structural integrity failure can lead to catastrophic consequences, including vehicle rollover, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: excessive damage to the vehicle's body or frame

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Tread Wear and Insufficient Traction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire tread wear and insufficient traction can lead to loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially on wet roads.
symptoms: tires lose traction on wet roads
vehicle skids or slides on wet roads
